# Book: Acts

# Section: The first book I wrote, Theophilus
# Acts 01:01
The first book I wrote, Theophilus,
concerned all that Jesus began both to do and to teach,
# Acts 01:02
until the day in which he was received up,
after he had given commandment
through the Holy Spirit
to the apostles whom he had chosen.

# Acts 01:03
To these he also showed himself alive after he suffered,
by many proofs,
appearing to them over a period of forty days
and speaking about God's Kingdom.

# Section: Being assembled together with them
# Acts 01:04
Being assembled together with them,
he commanded them,
{
  Don't depart from Jerusalem,
  but wait for the promise of the Father,
  which you heard from me.

  # Acts 01:05
  For John indeed baptized in water,
  but you will be baptized in the Holy Spirit
  not many days from now.
}

# Acts 01:06
Therefore,
when they had come together,
they asked him,
{
  Lord,
  are you now restoring the kingdom to Israel?
}

# Acts 01:07
He said to them,
{
  It isn't for you to know times or seasons
  which the Father has set within his own authority.

  # Acts 01:08
  But you will receive power
  when the Holy Spirit has come upon you.

  You will be witnesses to me in Jerusalem,
  in all Judea and Samaria,
  and to the uttermost parts of the earth.
}

# Section: When he had said these things,
# Acts 01:09
When he had said these things,
as they were looking,
he was taken up,
and a cloud received him out of their sight.

# Acts 01:10
While they were looking steadfastly
  into the sky
  as he went,
behold,
two men stood by them
  in white clothing,
# Acts 01:11
who also said,
{
  You men of Galilee,
  why do you stand looking into the sky?

  This Jesus,
  who was received up from you into the sky,
  will come back
  in the same way
  as you saw him going
  into the sky.
}

# Section: Then they returned to Jerusalem
# Acts 01:12
Then they returned to Jerusalem
from the mountain called Olivet,
which is near Jerusalem,
a Sabbath day's journey away.

# Acts 01:13
When they had come in,
they went up into the upper room where they were staying,
that is Peter,
John,
James,
Andrew,
Philip,
Thomas,
Bartholomew,
Matthew,
James the son of Alphaeus,
Simon the Zealot,
and Judas the son of James.

# Acts 01:14
All these with one accord continued steadfastly in prayer and supplication,
along with the women and Mary the mother of Jesus,
and with his brothers.

# Acts 01:15
In these days,
Peter stood up in the middle of the disciples (and the number of names was about one hundred twenty),
and said,
# Acts 01:16
{
  Brothers,
  it was necessary that this Scripture should be fulfilled,
  which the Holy Spirit spoke before
  by the mouth of David
  concerning Judas,
  who was guide to those who took Jesus.

  # Acts 01:17
  For he was counted with us,
  and received his portion in this ministry.

  # Acts 01:18
  Now this man obtained a field with the reward for his wickedness;
  and falling headlong,
  his body burst open and all his intestines gushed out.

  # Acts 01:19
  It became known to everyone who lived in Jerusalem
  that in their language that field was called ‘Akeldama,’
  that is, ‘The field of blood.’

  # Acts 01:20
  For it is written in the book of Psalms,
  {
    Let his habitation be made desolate.

    Let no one dwell in it;
  }

  and,
  {
    Let another take his office.
  }

  # Acts 01:21
  Of the men therefore
  who have accompanied us all the time
  that the Lord Jesus went in and out among us,
  # Acts 01:22
  beginning from the baptism of John
  to the day that he was received up from us,
  of these one must become a witness with us
  of his resurrection.
}

# Acts 01:23
They put forward two:
Joseph called Barsabbas,
who was also called Justus,
and Matthias.

# Acts 01:24
They prayed and said,
{
  You, Lord,
  who know the hearts of all men,
  show which one of these two you have chosen
  # Acts 01:25
  to take part in this ministry and apostleship from which Judas fell away,
  that he might go to his own place.
}

# Acts 01:26
They drew lots for them,
and the lot fell on Matthias;
and he was counted with the eleven apostles.

# Acts 02:01
Now when the day of Pentecost had come,
they were all with one accord in one place.

# Acts 02:02
Suddenly there came from the sky a sound like the rushing of a mighty wind,
and it filled all the house where they were sitting.

# Acts 02:03
Tongues like fire appeared and were distributed to them,
and one sat on each of them.

# Acts 02:04
They were all filled with the Holy Spirit
and began to speak with other languages,
as the Spirit gave them the ability to speak.

# Acts 02:05
Now there were dwelling in Jerusalem Jews,
devout men,
from every nation under the sky.

# Acts 02:06
When this sound was heard,
the multitude came together and were bewildered,
because everyone heard them speaking in his own language.

# Acts 02:07
They were all amazed and marveled,
saying to one another,
{
  Behold,
  aren't all these who speak Galileans?

  # Acts 02:08
  How do we hear,
  everyone in our own native language?

  # Acts 02:09
  Parthians,
  Medes,
  Elamites,
  and people from Mesopotamia,
  Judea,
  Cappadocia,
  Pontus,
  Asia,
  # Acts 02:10
  Phrygia,
  Pamphylia,
  Egypt,
  the parts of Libya around Cyrene,
  visitors from Rome,
  both Jews and proselytes,
  # Acts 02:11
  Cretans and Arabians ---
  we hear them speaking in our languages
  the mighty works of God!
}

# Acts 02:12
They were all amazed and were perplexed,
saying to one another,
{
  What does this mean?
}

# Acts 02:13
Others,
mocking,
said,
{
  They are filled with new wine.
}

# Acts 02:14
But Peter,
standing up with the eleven,
lifted up his voice and spoke out to them,
{
  You men of Judea and all you who dwell at Jerusalem,
  let this be known to you,
  and listen to my words.

  # Acts 02:15
  For these aren't drunken,
  as you suppose,
  seeing it is only the third hour of the day.

  # Acts 02:16
  But this is what has been spoken through the prophet Joel:
  # Acts 02:17
  {
    It will be in the last days,
    says God,
    that I will pour out my Spirit on all flesh.

    Your sons and your daughters will prophesy.

    Your young men will see visions.

    Your old men will dream dreams.

    # Acts 02:18
    Yes,
    and on my servants and on my handmaidens in those days,
    I will pour out my Spirit,
    and they will prophesy.

    # Acts 02:19
    I will show wonders in the sky above,
    and signs on the earth beneath:
    blood,
    and fire,
    and billows of smoke.

    # Acts 02:20
    The sun will be turned into darkness,
    and the moon into blood,
    before the great and glorious day of the Lord comes.

    # Acts 02:21
    It will be that whoever will call on the name of the Lord will be saved.
  }

  # Acts 02:22
  Men of Israel, hear these words!

  Jesus of Nazareth,
  a man approved by God to you
  by mighty works and wonders and signs
  which God did by him among you,
  even as you yourselves know,
  # Acts 02:23
  him,
  being delivered up
  by the determined counsel and foreknowledge of God,
  you have taken by the hand of lawless men,
  crucified and killed;
  # Acts 02:24
  whom God raised up,
  having freed him from the agony of death,
  because it was not possible that he should be held by it.

  # Acts 02:25
  For David says concerning him,
  {
    I saw the Lord always before my face,
    for he is on my right hand,
    that I should not be moved.

    # Acts 02:26
    Therefore my heart was glad,
    and my tongue rejoiced.

    Moreover my flesh also will dwell in hope,
    # Acts 02:27
    because you will not leave my soul in Hades,
    neither will you allow your Holy One to see decay.

    # Acts 02:28
    You made known to me the ways of life.

    You will make me full of gladness with your presence.
  }

  # Acts 02:29
  Brothers,
  I may tell you freely of the patriarch David,
  that he both died and was buried,
  and his tomb is with us to this day.

  # Acts 02:30
  Therefore,
  being a prophet,
  and knowing that God had sworn
  with an oath
  to him
  that of the fruit of his body,
  according to the flesh,
  he would raise up the Christ
  to sit on his throne,
  # Acts 02:31
  he foreseeing this,
  spoke about the resurrection of the Christ,
  that his soul wasn't left in Hades,
  and his flesh didn't see decay.

  # Acts 02:32
  This Jesus God raised up,
  to which we all are witnesses.

  # Acts 02:33
  Being therefore exalted by the right hand of God,
  and having received from the Father the promise of the Holy Spirit,
  he has poured out this which you now see and hear.

  # Acts 02:34
  For David didn't ascend into the heavens,
  but he says himself,
  {
    The Lord said to my Lord,
    {
      Sit by my right hand
      # Acts 02:35
      until I make your enemies a footstool for your feet.
    }
  }

  # Acts 02:36
  Let all the house of Israel
  therefore know certainly
  that God has made him both Lord and Christ,
  this Jesus whom you crucified.
}

# Acts 02:37
Now when they heard this,
they were cut to the heart,
and said to Peter and the rest of the apostles,
{
  Brothers, what shall we do?
}

# Acts 02:38
Peter said to them,
{
  Repent and be baptized,
  every one of you,
  in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of sins,
  and you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.

  # Acts 02:39
  For the promise is to you and to your children,
  and to all who are far off,
  even as many as the Lord our God will call to himself.
}

# Acts 02:40
With many other words he testified and exhorted them,
saying,
{
  Save yourselves from this crooked generation!
}

# Acts 02:41
Then those who gladly received his word were baptized.

There were added that day about three thousand souls.

# Acts 02:42
They continued steadfastly in the apostles' teaching and fellowship,
in the breaking of bread,
and prayer.

# Acts 02:43
Fear came on every soul,
and many wonders and signs were done through the apostles.

# Acts 02:44
All who believed were together,
and had all things in common.

# Acts 02:45
They sold their possessions and goods,
and distributed them to all,
according as anyone had need.

# Acts 02:46
Day by day,
continuing steadfastly with one accord in the temple,
and breaking bread at home,
they took their food with gladness and singleness of heart,
# Acts 02:47
praising God and having favor with all the people.

The Lord added to the assembly
day by day
those who were being saved.

# Acts 03:01
Peter and John were going up into the temple at the hour of prayer,
the ninth hour.

# Acts 03:02
A certain man who was lame from his mother's womb was being carried,
whom they laid daily at the door of the temple which is called Beautiful,
to ask gifts for the needy of those who entered into the temple.

# Acts 03:03
Seeing Peter and John about to go into the temple,
he asked to receive gifts for the needy.

# Acts 03:04
Peter,
fastening his eyes on him,
with John,
said,
{
  Look at us.
}

# Acts 03:05
He listened to them,
expecting to receive something from them.

# Acts 03:06
But Peter said,
{
  I have no silver or gold,
  but what I have,
  that I give you.

  In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth,
  get up and walk!
}

# Acts 03:07
He took him by the right hand and raised him up.

Immediately his feet and his ankle bones received strength.

# Acts 03:08
Leaping up,
he stood and began to walk.

He entered with them into the temple,
walking,
leaping,
and praising God.

# Acts 03:09
All the people saw him walking and praising God.

# Acts 03:10
They recognized him,
that it was he who used to sit
begging for gifts for the needy
at the Beautiful Gate of the temple.

They were filled with wonder and amazement
at what had happened to him.

# Acts 03:11
As the lame man who was healed held on to Peter and John,
all the people ran together to them in the porch that is called Solomon's,
greatly wondering.

# Acts 03:12
When Peter saw it,
he responded to the people,
{
  You men of Israel,
  why do you marvel at this man?

  Why do you fasten your eyes on us,
  as though by our own power or godliness we had made him walk?

  # Acts 03:13
  The God of Abraham,
  Isaac,
  and Jacob,
  the God of our fathers,
  has glorified his Servant Jesus,
  whom you delivered up and denied in the presence of Pilate,
  when he had determined to release him.

  # Acts 03:14
  But you denied the Holy and Righteous One and asked for a murderer to be granted to you,
  # Acts 03:15
  and killed the Prince of life,
  whom God raised from the dead,
  to which we are witnesses.

  # Acts 03:16
  By faith in his name,
  his name has made this man strong,
  whom you see and know.

  Yes,
  the faith which is through him has given him this perfect soundness in the presence of you all.

  # Acts 03:17
  Now,
  brothers,
  I know that you did this in ignorance,
  as did also your rulers.

  # Acts 03:18
  But the things which God announced by the mouth of all his prophets,
  that Christ should suffer,
  he thus fulfilled.

  # Acts 03:19
  Repent therefore,
  and turn again,
  that your sins may be blotted out,
  so that there may come times of refreshing from the presence of the Lord,

  # Acts 03:20
  and that he may send Christ Jesus,
  who was ordained for you before,
  # Acts 03:21
  whom heaven must receive until the times of restoration of all things,
  which God spoke long ago by the mouth of his holy prophets.

  # Acts 03:22
  For Moses indeed said to the fathers,
  {
    The Lord God will raise up a prophet
    for you
    from among your brothers,
    like me.

    You shall listen to him in all things whatever he says to you.

    # Acts 03:23
    It will be that every soul
    that will not listen
    to that prophet
    will be utterly destroyed
    from among the people.
  }

  # Acts 03:24
  Yes,
  and all the prophets from Samuel and those who followed after,
  as many as have spoken,
  also told of these days.

  # Acts 03:25
  You are the children of the prophets,
  and of the covenant which God made with our fathers,
  saying to Abraham,
  {
    All the families of the earth will be blessed through your offspring.
  }

  # Acts 03:26
  God,
  having raised up his servant Jesus,
  sent him to you first to bless you,
  in turning away every one of you from your wickedness.
}

# Acts 04:01
As they spoke to the people,
the priests
and the captain of the temple
and the Sadducees
came to them,
# Acts 04:02
being upset
because they taught the people
and proclaimed in Jesus
the resurrection from the dead.

# Acts 04:03
They laid hands on them,
and put them in custody until the next day,
for it was now evening.

# Acts 04:04
But many of those who heard the word believed,
and the number of the men came to be about five thousand.

# Acts 04:05
In the morning,
their rulers,
elders,
and scribes were gathered together in Jerusalem.

# Acts 04:06
Annas the high priest was there,
with Caiaphas,
John,
Alexander,
and as many as were relatives of the high priest.

# Acts 04:07
When they had stood Peter and John in the middle of them,
they inquired,
{
  By what power,
  or in what name,
  have you done this?
}

# Acts 04:08
Then Peter,
filled with the Holy Spirit,
said to them,
{
  You rulers of the people and elders of Israel,
  # Acts 04:09
  if we are examined today concerning a good deed done to a crippled man,
  by what means this man has been healed,
  # Acts 04:10
  may it be known to you all,
  and to all the people of Israel,
  that in the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth,
  whom you crucified,
  whom God raised from the dead,
  this man stands here before you whole in him.

  # Acts 04:11
  He is
  {
    the stone which was regarded as worthless by you,
    the builders,
    which has become the head of the corner.
  }

  # Acts 04:12
  There is salvation in no one else,
  for there is no other name under heaven that is given among men,
  by which we must be saved!
}

# Acts 04:13
Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John,
and had perceived that they were unlearned and ignorant men,
they marveled.

They recognized that they had been with Jesus.

# Acts 04:14
Seeing the man who was healed standing with them,
they could say nothing against it.

# Acts 04:15
But when they had commanded them to go aside out of the council,
they conferred among themselves,
# Acts 04:16
saying,
{
  What shall we do to these men?

  Because indeed a notable miracle has been done through them,
  as can be plainly seen by all who dwell in Jerusalem,
  and we can't deny it.

  # Acts 04:17
  But so that this spreads no further among the people,
  let's threaten them,
  that from now on they don't speak to anyone in this name.
}

# Acts 04:18
They called them,
and commanded them not to speak at all nor teach in the name of Jesus.

# Acts 04:19
But Peter and John answered them,
{
  Whether it is right in the sight of God to listen to you rather than to God,
  judge for yourselves,
  # Acts 04:20
  for we can't help telling the things which we saw and heard.
}

# Acts 04:21
When they had further threatened them,
they let them go,
finding no way to punish them,
because of the people;
for everyone glorified God for that which was done.

# Acts 04:22
For the man on whom this miracle of healing was performed was more than forty years old.

# Acts 04:23
Being let go,
they came to their own company
and reported all
that the chief priests and the elders had said to them.

# Acts 04:24
When they heard it,
they lifted up their voice to God with one accord and said,
{
  O Lord,
  you are God,
  who made the heaven,
  the earth,
  the sea,
  and all that is in them;
  # Acts 04:25
  who by the mouth of your servant David,
  said,
  {
    Why do the nations rage,
    and the peoples plot a vain thing?

    # Acts 04:26
    The kings of the earth take a stand,
    and the rulers plot together,
    against the Lord,
    and against his Christ.
  }

  # Acts 04:27
  For truly,
  both Herod and Pontius Pilate,
  with the Gentiles and the people of Israel,
  were gathered together against your holy servant Jesus,
  whom you anointed,
  # Acts 04:28
  to do whatever your hand and your counsel foreordained to happen.

  # Acts 04:29
  Now, Lord,
  look at their threats,
  and grant to your servants to speak your word with all boldness,
  # Acts 04:30
  while you stretch out your hand to heal;
  and that signs and wonders may be done through the name of your holy Servant Jesus.
}

# Acts 04:31
When they had prayed,
the place was shaken where they were gathered together.

They were all filled with the Holy Spirit,
and they spoke the word of God with boldness.

# Acts 04:32
The multitude of those who believed were of one heart and soul.

Not one of them claimed that anything of the things which he possessed was his own,
but they had all things in common.

# Acts 04:33
With great power,
the apostles gave their testimony of the resurrection of the Lord Jesus.

Great grace was on them all.

# Acts 04:34
For neither was there among them any who lacked,
for as many as were owners of lands or houses sold them,
and brought the proceeds of the things that were sold,

# Acts 04:35
and laid them at the apostles' feet;
and distribution was made to each,
according as anyone had need.

# Acts 04:36
Joses,
who by the apostles was also called Barnabas (which is,
being interpreted,
Son of Encouragement),
a Levite,
a man of Cyprus by race,
# Acts 04:37
having a field,
sold it and brought the money and laid it at the apostles' feet.

# Acts 05:01
But a certain man named Ananias,
with Sapphira his wife,
sold a possession,
# Acts 05:02
and kept back part of the price,
his wife also being aware of it,
then brought a certain part and laid it at the apostles' feet.

# Acts 05:03
But Peter said,
{
  Ananias,
  why has Satan
  filled your heart
  to lie
  to the Holy Spirit
  and to keep back part of the price of the land?

  # Acts 05:04
  While you kept it,
  didn't it remain your own?

  After it was sold,
  wasn't it in your power?

  How is it that you have conceived this thing in your heart?

  You haven't lied to men,
  but to God.
}

# Acts 05:05
Ananias,
hearing these words,
fell down and died.

Great fear came on all who heard these things.

# Acts 05:06
The young men arose and wrapped him up,
and they carried him out and buried him.

# Acts 05:07
About three hours later,
his wife,
not knowing what had happened,
came in.

# Acts 05:08
Peter answered her,
{
  Tell me whether you sold the land for so much.
}

She said,
{
  Yes, for so much.
}

# Acts 05:09
But Peter asked her,
{
  How is it that you have agreed together to tempt the Spirit of the Lord?

  Behold,
  the feet of those who have buried your husband are at the door,
  and they will carry you out.
}

# Acts 05:10
She fell down immediately at his feet and died.

The young men came in and found her dead,
and they carried her out and buried her by her husband.

# Acts 05:11
Great fear came on the whole assembly,
and on all who heard these things.

# Acts 05:12
By the hands of the apostles
many signs and wonders were done
among the people.

They were all with one accord in Solomon's porch.

# Acts 05:13
None of the rest dared to join them;
however,
the people honored them.

# Acts 05:14
More believers were added to the Lord,
multitudes of both men and women.

# Acts 05:15
They even carried out the sick into the streets and laid them on cots and mattresses,
so that as Peter came by,
at least his shadow might overshadow some of them.

# Acts 05:16
The multitude also came together from the cities around Jerusalem,
bringing sick people and those who were tormented by unclean spirits;
and they were all healed.

# Acts 05:17
But the high priest rose up,
and all those who were with him (which is the sect of the Sadducees),
and they were filled with jealousy
# Acts 05:18
and laid hands on the apostles,
then put them in public custody.

# Acts 05:19
But an angel of the Lord opened the prison doors by night,
and brought them out and said,
# Acts 05:20
{
  Go stand and speak in the temple to the people all the words of this life.
}

# Acts 05:21
When they heard this,
they entered into the temple about daybreak and taught.

But the high priest and those who were with him came and called the council together,
with all the senate of the children of Israel,
and sent to the prison to have them brought.

# Acts 05:22
But the officers who came didn't find them in the prison.

They returned and reported,
# Acts 05:23
{
  We found the prison shut and locked,
  and the guards standing before the doors,
  but when we opened them,
  we found no one inside!
}

# Acts 05:24
Now when the high priest,
the captain of the temple,
and the chief priests heard these words,
they were very perplexed about them and what might become of this.

# Acts 05:25
One came and told them,
{
  Behold,
  the men whom you put in prison are in the temple,
  standing and teaching the people.
}

# Acts 05:26
Then the captain went with the officers,
and brought them without violence,
for they were afraid that the people might stone them.

# Acts 05:27
When they had brought them,
they set them before the council.

The high priest questioned them,
# Acts 05:28
saying,
{
  Didn't we strictly command you not to teach in this name?

  Behold,
  you have filled Jerusalem with your teaching,
  and intend to bring this man's blood on us.
}

# Acts 05:29
But Peter and the apostles answered,
{
  We must obey God rather than men.

  # Acts 05:30
  The God of our fathers raised up Jesus,
  whom you killed,
  hanging him on a tree.

  # Acts 05:31
  God exalted him with his right hand to be a Prince and a Savior,
  to give repentance to Israel,
  and remission of sins.

  # Acts 05:32
  We are his witnesses of these things;
  and so also is the Holy Spirit,
  whom God has given to those who obey him.
}

# Acts 05:33
But they,
when they heard this,
were cut to the heart,
and were determined to kill them.

# Acts 05:34
But one stood up in the council,
a Pharisee named Gamaliel,
a teacher of the law,
honored by all the people,
and commanded to put the apostles out for a little while.

# Acts 05:35
He said to them,
{
  You men of Israel,
  be careful concerning these men,
  what you are about to do.

  # Acts 05:36
  For before these days Theudas rose up,
  making himself out to be somebody;
  to whom a number of men,
  about four hundred,
  joined themselves.

  He was slain;
  and all,
  as many as obeyed him,
  were dispersed and came to nothing.

  # Acts 05:37
  After this man,
  Judas of Galilee rose up in the days of the enrollment,
  and drew away some people after him.

  He also perished,
  and all,
  as many as obeyed him,
  were scattered abroad.

  # Acts 05:38
  Now I tell you,
  withdraw from these men and leave them alone.

  For if this counsel or this work is of men,
  it will be overthrown.

  # Acts 05:39
  But if it is of God,
  you will not be able to overthrow it,
  and you would be found even to be fighting against God!
}

# Acts 05:40
They agreed with him.

Summoning the apostles,
they beat them and commanded them not to speak in the name of Jesus,
and let them go.

# Acts 05:41
