# Acts 27:17
After they had hoisted it up,
they used cables to help reinforce the ship.

Fearing that they would run aground on the Syrtis sand bars,
they lowered the sea anchor,
and so were driven along.

# Acts 27:18
As we labored exceedingly with the storm,
the next day they began to throw things overboard.

# Acts 27:19
On the third day,
they threw out the ship's tackle with their own hands.

# Acts 27:20
When neither sun nor stars shone on us for many days,
and no small storm pressed on us,
